          "gap": 10,
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "9Sv0u",
              "fill": "#22C55E",
              "content": "BUGS — FIXED",
              "fontFamily": "IBM Plex Mono",
              "fontSize": 11,
              "fontWeight": "700",
              "letterSpacing": 0.8
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "JjjGp",
              "fill": "#94A3B8",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "· UAyhv status bar showed \"LTE\" — all other screens use \"5G\". Fixed.",
              "lineHeight": 1.5,
              "fontFamily": "Geist",
              "fontSize": 13,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "GJevB",
              "fill": "#94A3B8",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "· Component/Processing Card width was 360px. All other card components are 320px. Fixed to 320.",
              "lineHeight": 1.5,
              "fontFamily": "Geist",
              "fontSize": 13,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "rectangle",
          "id": "7gHdV",
          "fill": "#1E293B",
          "width": "fill_container",
          "height": 1
        },
        {
          "type": "frame",
          "id": "Mz7pw",
          "name": "inconsist",
          "width": "fill_container",
          "layout": "vertical",
          "gap": 10,
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "H4sUW",
              "fill": "#F59E0B",
              "content": "INCONSISTENCIES",
              "fontFamily": "IBM Plex Mono",
              "fontSize": 11,
              "fontWeight": "700",
              "letterSpacing": 0.8
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "rmRL1",
              "fill": "#94A3B8",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "1. Font family split — Implementation flow (Steps 1–7) uses Inter. Course flow uses Geist. design.md prescribes Geist for all primary product text. The impl flow should migrate to Geist.",
              "lineHeight": 1.5,
              "fontFamily": "Geist",
              "fontSize": 13,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "O1grC",
              "fill": "#94A3B8",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "2. Back button shape mismatch — Course flow back btn is circular (radius 9999, fill #5151514d). Impl flow is a rounded square (radius 16, fill $white-5 + stroke). Comparison design below.",
              "lineHeight": 1.5,
              "fontFamily": "Geist",
              "fontSize": 13,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "wRq0F",
              "fill": "#94A3B8",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "3. Steps 6 & 7 break the header pattern — Steps 1–5 have a consistent shell: top bar with \"Generate Voice Profile\" title + step counter label + progress bar. Steps 6 and 7 drop both and invent a new pattern. Comparison design below.",
              "lineHeight": 1.5,
              "fontFamily": "Geist",
              "fontSize": 13,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "mascx",
              "fill": "#94A3B8",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "4. Empty space on processing screens — Steps 4 & 5 show the processing card then have ~300px of dead space before the CTA. Comparison design with improved use of that space below.",
              "lineHeight": 1.5,
              "fontFamily": "Geist",
              "fontSize": 13,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "HGrxz",
              "fill": "#94A3B8",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "5. Completion copy inconsistency — The chip reads \"Lesson completed\" but the heading reads \"Section complete\". Lesson and section are used interchangeably. Pick one.",
              "lineHeight": 1.5,
              "fontFamily": "Geist",
              "fontSize": 13,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "XQLfo",
              "fill": "#94A3B8",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "6. File Preview Actions (dggpf) — The \"Continue\" button is absolutely positioned (x:220, y:12) inside a flex row, bypassing the layout. This will break if the container resizes. Should be a flex child.",
              "lineHeight": 1.5,
              "fontFamily": "Geist",
              "fontSize": 13,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "rectangle",
          "id": "8ew7K",
          "fill": "#1E293B",
          "width": "fill_container",
          "height": 1
        },
        {
          "type": "frame",
          "id": "yoGPh",
          "name": "ux",
          "width": "fill_container",
          "layout": "vertical",
          "gap": 10,
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "M0sRq",
              "fill": "#60A5FA",
              "content": "UX FLOW NOTES",
              "fontFamily": "IBM Plex Mono",
              "fontSize": 11,
              "fontWeight": "700",
              "letterSpacing": 0.8
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "Clwob",
              "fill": "#94A3B8",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "Course flow: The Course Detail screen shows the Implementation Card alongside the lesson list, creating a competing CTA (Start Course vs Start Building Now). Consider visually de-emphasizing the impl card — it should be a secondary action.",
              "lineHeight": 1.5,
              "fontFamily": "Geist",
              "fontSize": 13,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "s1XGG",
              "fill": "#94A3B8",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "Completion screen: \"Continue to next lesson\" CTA doesn't clarify destination. After section complete, does the user go to the next card, back to course detail, or to a new section? Worth making the destination explicit (e.g. \"Start Section 2\").",
              "lineHeight": 1.5,
              "fontFamily": "Geist",
              "fontSize": 13,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "FaJ1k",
              "fill": "#94A3B8",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
